hh3cFcPsm.name: hh3cFcPsm

revisions.description: HH3C-FC-PSM-MIB module is for managing the implementation of FC port security.

hh3cFcPsm.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cFcPsm.description: This MIB contains the objects for FC port security.

Hh3cFcPsmPortBindDevType.name: Hh3cFcPsmPortBindDevType
Hh3cFcPsmPortBindDevType.description: The types of the instance of hh3cFcPsmLoginDev, including nWWN(Node World Wide Name), pWWN(Port World Wide Name), sWWN(Switch World Wide Name), and wildCard.

Hh3cFcPsmClearEntryType.name: Hh3cFcPsmClearEntryType
Hh3cFcPsmClearEntryType.description: This object when set to clearStatic, results in port bind static entries being cleared on this VSAN(Virtual Storage Area Networks). This object when set to clearAutoLearn, results in port bind auto-learnt entries being cleared on this VSAN. This object when set to clearAll, results in all of the port bind entries being cleared on this VSAN. No action is taken if this object is set to noop. The value of this object when read is always noop.

hh3cFcPsmNotifyEnable.name: hh3cFcPsmNotifyEnable
hh3cFcPsmNotifyEnable.description: Whether to generate the notification or not depends on the object.

hh3cFcPsmEnableTable.name: hh3cFcPsmEnableTable
hh3cFcPsmEnableTable.description: Enable or disable the port security feature on a specified VSAN.

hh3cFcPsmEnableEntry.name: hh3cFcPsmEnableEntry
hh3cFcPsmEnableEntry.description: Detailed information about the port security.

hh3cFcPsmEnableVsanIndex.name: hh3cFcPsmEnableVsanIndex
hh3cFcPsmEnableVsanIndex.description: The ID of VSAN on this entry.

hh3cFcPsmEnable.name: hh3cFcPsmEnable
hh3cFcPsmEnable.description: When set to enable, the port security is on, the value of hh3cFcPsmEnableState will be true. When set to enableWithAutoLearn, the port security is on with auto-learning, the value of hh3cFcPsmEnableState will be true. When set to disable, the port security is off, the value of hh3cFcPsmEnableState will be false. The noop means no action. The value of this object when read is always noop.

hh3cFcPsmEnableState.name: hh3cFcPsmEnableState
hh3cFcPsmEnableState.description: The state of the port security. When the value is true, it means the port security is on, while the false means the port security is off.

hh3cFcPsmConfigTable.name: hh3cFcPsmConfigTable
hh3cFcPsmConfigTable.description: A table that contains the configured entries.

hh3cFcPsmLoginDevType.name: hh3cFcPsmLoginDevType
hh3cFcPsmLoginDevType.description: This represents the type of the instance of hh3cFcPsmLoginDev, which includes nWWN, pWWN, sWWN, and wildCard.

hh3cFcPsmLoginDev.name: hh3cFcPsmLoginDev
hh3cFcPsmLoginDev.description: The logging-in device name, which is decided by the hh3cFcPsmLoginDevType object. It represents node WWN when the value of hh3cFcPsmLoginDevType is nWWN. It represents port WWN when the value of hh3cFcPsmLoginDevType is pWWN. It represents switch WWN when the value of hh3cFcPsmLoginDevType is sWWN. It represents any device when the value of hh3cFcPsmLoginDevType is wildCard, and the value of the instance of this object should be zero-length string. The value of this object should not be invalid when hh3cFcPsmRowStatus is set to createAndGo or active.

hh3cFcPsmLoginPoint.name: hh3cFcPsmLoginPoint
hh3cFcPsmLoginPoint.description: The address of the port on the local switch through which the instance of hh3cFcPsmLoginDev can log in. It represents ifindex when the value is not zero. It represents any port when the value is zero.

hh3cFcPsmRowStatus.name: hh3cFcPsmRowStatus
hh3cFcPsmRowStatus.description: Entry status. When creating a new instance of this table, the following objects should be set simultaneously: hh3cFcPsmLoginDevType, h3cFcPsmLoginDev, hh3cFcPsmLoginPoint, hh3cFcPsmRowStatus. If hh3cFcPsmLoginDevType is set to wildCard, the value of the instance of hh3cFcPsmLoginDev should be zero-length string. The value of hh3cFcPsmLoginDevType and hh3cFcPsmLoginPoint cannot be set to wildCard and zero at the same time.

hh3cFcPsmEnfTable.name: hh3cFcPsmEnfTable
hh3cFcPsmEnfTable.description: The FC port security enforced table. It contains not only the configured policies, but also the learning ones learnt by the switch itself.

hh3cFcPsmEnfEntry.name: hh3cFcPsmEnfEntry
hh3cFcPsmEnfEntry.description: Detailed information about the FC port security enforced policy.

hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDevType.name: hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDevType
hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDevType.description: This represents the type of the instance of hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDev, which includes nWWN, pWWN, sWWN, and wildCard.

hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDev.name: hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDev
hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDev.description: The logging-in device name, which is decided by the hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDevType object. It represents node WWN when the value of hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDevType is nWWN. It represents port WWN when the value of hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDevType is pWWN. It represents switch WWN when the value of hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDevType is sWWN. It represents any device when the value of hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDevType is wildCard, and the value of the instance of this object should be zero-length string.

hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginPoint.name: hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginPoint
hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginPoint.description: The address of the port on the local switch through which the instance of hh3cFcPsmEnfLoginDev can log in. It represents ifindex when the value is not zero. It represents any port when the value is zero.

hh3cFcPsmEnfEntryType.name: hh3cFcPsmEnfEntryType
hh3cFcPsmEnfEntryType.description: When the value is learning, it represents the entry is learnt by the switch itself temporarily and will be deleted when the device log out. When the value is learnt, it represents the entry is learnt by the switch permanently. When the value is static, it represents the entry is configured.

hh3cFcPsmCopyToConfigTable.name: hh3cFcPsmCopyToConfigTable
hh3cFcPsmCopyToConfigTable.description: Specifies whether to copy the entries from enforced table to the ones on configured table.

hh3cFcPsmCopyToConfig.name: hh3cFcPsmCopyToConfig
hh3cFcPsmCopyToConfig.description: When the object is set to copy, the learned entries will be copied on to the configured table on this VSAN, while the noop means no operation. The value of this object when read is always noop.

hh3cFcPsmAutoLearnTable.name: hh3cFcPsmAutoLearnTable
hh3cFcPsmAutoLearnTable.description: This table shows whether the auto-learning is enabled or not on specific VSANs.

hh3cFcPsmAutoLearnEnable.name: hh3cFcPsmAutoLearnEnable
hh3cFcPsmAutoLearnEnable.description: This object is set to true to enable, or false to disable auto-learning on the local switch. When set to true, the switch can learn the devices that have already logged in as learning entries on the enforced table, while the false can stop the learning operation with the learning entries transformed to learnt ones.

hh3cFcPsmClearTable.name: hh3cFcPsmClearTable
hh3cFcPsmClearTable.description: This table is used for cleaning specific entries in enforced table.

hh3cFcPsmClearEntry.name: hh3cFcPsmClearEntry
hh3cFcPsmClearEntry.description: Detailed information about the cleaning options.

hh3cFcPsmClearType.name: hh3cFcPsmClearType
hh3cFcPsmClearType.description: This object when set to clearStatic, results in port bind static entries being cleared on this VSAN. This object when set to clearAutoLearn, results in auto-learnt entries being cleared on this VSAN. This object when set to clearAll, results in all of the port bind entries being cleared on this VSAN. No action is taken if this object is set to noop. The value of this object when read is always noop.

hh3cFcPsmClearIntf.name: hh3cFcPsmClearIntf
hh3cFcPsmClearIntf.description: The object specifies the interface on which the entries will be cleared. If the object is zero or not set, it means the specified entries on all interfaces will be cleared.

hh3cFcPsmStatsTable.name: hh3cFcPsmStatsTable
hh3cFcPsmStatsTable.description: This table contains statistics of devices, which had been allowed or denied to log into the switch.

hh3cFcPsmAllowedLogins.name: hh3cFcPsmAllowedLogins
hh3cFcPsmAllowedLogins.description: The number of requests that have been allowed on the specified VSAN.

hh3cFcPsmDeniedLogins.name: hh3cFcPsmDeniedLogins
hh3cFcPsmDeniedLogins.description: The number of requests that have been denied on the specified VSAN.

hh3cFcPsmStatsClear.name: hh3cFcPsmStatsClear
hh3cFcPsmStatsClear.description: The statistics on this VSAN will be cleared if this object is set to clear. No action is taken if this object is set to noop. The value of this object when read is always noop.

hh3cFcPsmViolationTable.name: hh3cFcPsmViolationTable
hh3cFcPsmViolationTable.description: This table maintains the information about the violations happened, containing at most 1024 items. When the number exceeds 1024, the earliest item will be over-written.

hh3cFcPsmViolationIndex.name: hh3cFcPsmViolationIndex
hh3cFcPsmViolationIndex.description: The index of this entry. The entry is uniquely distinguished by WWN, WWN type and ifindex where the login was denied.

hh3cFcPsmLoginPWWN.name: hh3cFcPsmLoginPWWN
hh3cFcPsmLoginPWWN.description: The pWWN of the device whose FLOGI(Fabric Login) request had been denied. If the device is an n-node, the value of the instance of hh3cFcPsmLoginSWWN should be zero-length string.

hh3cFcPsmLoginNWWN.name: hh3cFcPsmLoginNWWN
hh3cFcPsmLoginNWWN.description: The nWWN of the device whose FLOGI request had been denied. If the device is an n-node, the value of the instance of hh3cFcPsmLoginSWWN should be zero-length string.

hh3cFcPsmLoginSWWN.name: hh3cFcPsmLoginSWWN
hh3cFcPsmLoginSWWN.description: The sWWN of the device whose FLOGI request had been denied. If the device is a switch, the values of the instance of hh3cFcPsmLoginPWWN and hh3cFcPsmLoginNWWN should be zero-length string.

hh3cFcPsmLoginIntf.name: hh3cFcPsmLoginIntf
hh3cFcPsmLoginIntf.description: The ifindex of the port where the login was denied.

hh3cFcPsmLoginTime.name: hh3cFcPsmLoginTime
hh3cFcPsmLoginTime.description: Specifies the value of SysUpTime when the last denied login happened.

hh3cFcPsmLoginCount.name: hh3cFcPsmLoginCount
hh3cFcPsmLoginCount.description: The number of times for a certain nWWN/pWWN or sWWN had been denied to log into an interface of the local device.

hh3cFcPsmFPortDenyNotify.name: hh3cFcPsmFPortDenyNotify
hh3cFcPsmFPortDenyNotify.description: Notifies that a FLOGI is denied on an F port of the local device.

hh3cFcPsmEPortDenyNotify.name: hh3cFcPsmEPortDenyNotify
hh3cFcPsmEPortDenyNotify.description: Notifies that a switch is denied on an E port of the local device.
